<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="inform-vt">inform <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪn'fɔːm/    美 /ɪn'fɔːrm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>[正式用语] 通知；告诉</strong></h4>
<p>to tell sb about sth, especially in an official way：</p>
<ul>
<li>inform sb about / of sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Bees fly in circles to inform their partners about / of food or danger.
蜜蜂跳圆形舞以告诉同伴食物的位置，或它们是否有危险。</p><footer>译林③ – 2改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>inform sb + (that) / wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We would like to inform all passengers that the restaurant car is now open.
我们想通知所有乘客，餐车现在开始营业。</p></div></div>